			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This post directly deals with this. Must have just missed reading this.
<br />

<br />
After reading this article, <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=1756," target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=1756,</a> by Spikey_Bloodaxe I began to wonder why our largest nuke, Firebolt of Tallon, wasn't increased by 20% in GoD and a substantial portion of our dps, PETS, weren't increased in dps by the same margin. 
<br />

<br />
Let assume we have three purely dps classes with two of those classes performing all of their damage through one means (wizards and nukes, rogues and melee) and one performing their damage through a mixture of skills (mages with nukes and pets). To upgrade the Wizard and Rogue's DPS, one only needs to increase 
<br />
A. Nukes for Wizards and 
<br />
B. Increase Weapon Damage for Rogues. 
<br />
With GoD there was a 20% increase to to the highest wizard spell and approxiametly a 20% increase to weapon damage for rogues. 
<br />

<br />
Now lets take the class that deals damage in 2 ways (mage). To increase the damage done by mages on the same linear fashion that you do wizards and rogues you need to upgrade not only the nuke by 20% but you need to upgrade the pet's max hit by 20%. This way the combined total of damage done by mages isnt just a percent increase of the partial damage (nukes) but is a full increase in the mages class dps by increasing pets with nukes. 
<br />

<br />
The problem arises for mages, however, that not only did our highest damaging nuke not get the 20% increase in power but our pet damage didn't get a corresponding increase of 20%. Now fast forward to OoW. 
<br />

<br />
In OoW it appears that there is a standard 30% increase to spell damage from GoD. For Wizards and rogues this is an easy problem to scale, simply increase spell damage by 30% and increase melee weapon damage by 30%. For mages it becomes tougher. 
<br />

<br />
Since our highest damaging nuke wasnt increased by 20% in GoD then a standard 30% increase to our spells isnt going to work. The same is true for our pets. The problem is that SOE increased our highest damaging nuke by 30% (remember that our nukes arent increased in GoD so that puts us one expansion behind other dps classes) and our pets our increased by 30% max hit from our PoP pets and not from a GoD pet with improved damage. 
<br />

<br />
If you look at the max hit of our water pet from PoP (Back stab 243, damage 81) and the max hit from our water pet in OoW (Back Stab 304, damage 102) you can see that the max hit of the water pet has been increased by roughly 30%. We run into the problem that we had before with our nukes (firebolt of tallon... and our OoW firebolt) we have missed an expansion of increase to our power. 
<br />

<br />
The OoW water pet should really have been 20% increase from PoP (to make up for GoD) then and additional 30% onto that pet. This would make the Water pet damage for OoW be 126 damage (81*1.20=97.20, 97.20*1.30=126.36) and the max Back Stab being 379 (243*1.20=291.60, 291.60*1.30=379.08). These increase should not only happen to the water pet but to all pets to compensate for the mages complex nature of 2 combined ways of dealing damage. 
<br />

<br />
Thank You, 
<br />
Biltil[/b]</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
